Class Result<T,E extends Throwable>

Direct Known Subclasses:
Result.R
@Immutable public class Result<T,E extends Throwable> extends Object implements Immutable
This class encapsulates a result of an operation that can either be a value of type T or an exception of type E. The class implements the Immutable interface, indicating that instances of this class are immutable. The class is parameterized by two types: T which is the type of the result value, and E which is the type of the exception. The exception type E is constrained to be a subtype of Throwable.
